Branson Mo. 
Oct 28-1922. 
My Dear little girl-
I don't just remember where I left off in my last letter to you. I think tho I was in the throes of a Tick Contest and the weather still very hot. I am surely glad to report that old "Lol" sums to have exausted himself and like wise the "Tick." The weather is very fine and the hills are gorgeous in their array of red and yellow How we have wished for you, you <unclear/> so thoroughly <unclear/> it all. Swimming is gone too. has been for some time. long before the heat abated, simply because the streams just dried up because of the big drought. "Blue hole" is a watching place for the horses and cows for miles around. Our well went dry. JOhn's cistern went dry and I had not very much water in my cistern. We had to have water hauled and put into John's cistern and we used magic for hours purposes. We could get two pails a day from the <unclear/> which made us drinking water and just think of this, John away, the water condition as I have described and this house on <unclear/> I never saw people gather as they did here. in 15 minutes there must ahve been 45 men here and all the women in the neighborhood <unclear/> 

