it water they had in the house some Even best <unclear/> paris with <unclear/> water. Thank the Lord it was put out before much damage was done it caught in John's Literary form the chimney they got insurance and Mona had all the traces obliterated before John returned. Oh I have so many things to tell you and if I tell them all there will be no other letters writen-Toning back I must tell you that I am going to Omaha sometime in Nov. John's portrait was finished <unclear/> he was there this time, and they are going to have a big time when it is placed in the Omaha Library and I am actually going to see it. And I had a letter from <unclear/> today <unclear/> me b-go on to Minnie after and spend the winter with her. I may, but that will have to develop yet. I surely want to go very much. <Unclear/> she worked for a whole month about <unclear/> women of us on our Street Carnival, Everything went fine and all the Carnival was just watching for the day to arrive to begin operations. It was to be the 6th of <unclear/>. and the night of the fourth and all day the 5th it poured rain the 6th was <unclear/> and cold and sloppy. None of the <unclear/> could be pent up in fact nothing could be done <unclear/> of doors. "As luck would have it" 

